  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed or flagged; 7 assessed factors show achieved levels below required levels at MRL 5; 6 factors not assessed represent epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo UQ campaign (n=500) was executed and demonstrated that rotor speed dominates hemolysis index variance. Despite the UQ campaign, model-form uncertainty remains unquantified and NIH predictions exceed measured values by up to a factor of 2.1. The credibility evidence package is structurally complete under the ProfileComplete conformance claim and is submitted for regulatory review. The assessment team notes that sensitivity findings from the UQ campaign are documented in Appendix C of the supporting technical report.",
